Sentencas: Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 (SDC)-embedded Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-delta (SSC) composite fibers were successfully fabricated by electrospinning using commercial SDC nanopowders and an SSC precursor gel containing polyvinyl alcohol (PVA) and hydrated metal nitrate.
Titulo: Performance evaluation of Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-δ fibers with embedded Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 particles as a solid oxide fuel cell composite cathode

Sentencas: After calcination of the composite fibers at 800 degrees C, the fibers of 300 +/- 80 nm in diameter with a well-developed SSC cubic-perovskite structure and fluorite SDC were successfully obtained.
Titulo: Performance evaluation of Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-δ fibers with embedded Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 particles as a solid oxide fuel cell composite cathode

Sentencas: An anode-supported single cell composed of NiO-Gd0.2Ce0.8O1.9 (GDC)/GDC/SSC-SDC fibers was fabricated, and its electrochemical performance was evaluated.
Titulo: Performance evaluation of Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-δ fibers with embedded Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 particles as a solid oxide fuel cell composite cathode

Sentencas: The maximum power densities were 1250 and 360 mW/cm(2) at 700 and 550 degrees C, respectively, which we ascribe to the excellent properties of the SSC fibers with embedded SDC particles such as a highly porous and continuous structure promoting mass transport and a charge transfer reaction.
Titulo: Performance evaluation of Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-δ fibers with embedded Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 particles as a solid oxide fuel cell composite cathode
